This paper investigates the influence of discourse features on text complexity assessment, which is a topic related to natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves the use of machine learning algorithms to analyze and compare different types of features, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of feature selection techniques, which is a common practice in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.CY).
